== Mitsue Jingū == {{Quotation| The Fudoki states: "In the {{ill|Uda District, Nara|lt=Uda District|ja|宇陀郡}}, in the village of Sasahata{{refnest|group="Note"|Now the Sasabata area of Hara Town, Yamabe 3.<ref name="taikeip421" />}}, stands the shrine of {{ill|Mitsue no Kami|ja|御杖の神}}. It does not enshrine the Great Spirit{{refnest|group="Note"|Meaning it does not enshrine the spirit of {{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照大神}}.<ref name="taikeip421" />}}. {{ill|Yamatohime-no-mikoto|lt=Yamatohime-no-Mikoto|ja|倭姫命|1=Yamatohime-no-mikoto}} carried Amaterasu on her head and, with her as the staff, reached this place. After searching for the shrine's location for three months, she finally established the divine fields as {{ill|Kanjin|ja|神戸}} (lands belonging to the shrine)." | ''Nihon Shoki Tsūshō, Volume 11''<ref name="taikei" />}}
