== Mitsue Jingū == {{Quotation| The Fudoki states: "In the [[:en:Uda District, Nara|Uda District]], in the village of Sasahata{{refnest|group="Note"|Now the Sasabata area of Hara Town, Yamabe 3.<ref name="taikeip421" />}}, stands the shrine of {{ill|Mitsue no Kami|ja|御杖の神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mitsue no Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. It does not enshrine the Great Spirit{{refnest|group="Note"|Meaning it does not enshrine the spirit of [[:en:Amaterasu|Amaterasu Ōmikami]].<ref name="taikeip421" />}}. [[:en:Yamatohime-no-mikoto|Yamatohime-no-Mikoto]] carried Amaterasu on her head and, with her as the staff, reached this place. After searching for the shrine's location for three months, she finally established the divine fields as {{ill|Kanjin|ja|神戸|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanjin|qq=}} (lands belonging to the shrine)." | ''Nihon Shoki Tsūshō, Volume 11''<ref name="taikei" />}}
