== Mitonomaguwai (Three Union Marriage) == {{Quotation| The ''Yamato no Kuni Fudoki'' states: "The {{ill|Amatsukami|ja|天津神|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amatsukami|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=天津神・国津神}} no Mikoto and {{ill|Ishizukami|ja|石津神|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ishizukami|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} no Mikoto engaged in a union known as 'Mitonomaguwai'{{refnest|group="Note"|Referring to the union of man and woman.<ref name="taikeip421">''Fudoki,'' {{ill|Iwanami Shoten|en|Iwanami Shoten|WD=Q1331427|lt=Iwanami Shoten|1=Iwanami Shoten}} Japanese Classical Literature Series 2, 14th edition, 1971 (1st edition, 1958), p.421, footnote.</ref>}}. They wandered in thought (''urabure''){{refnest|group="Note"|Meaning 'lost in thought.'<ref name="taikeip421" />}} and conversed face-to-face (''omogatari''){{refnest|group="Note"|Meaning 'direct conversation.'<ref name="taikeip421" />}}." | ''Bishamondōbon Kokinshūchū''<ref name="taikei">''Fudoki,'' Japanese Classical Literature Series 2, {{ill|Iwanami Shoten|en|Iwanami Shoten|WD=Q1331427|lt=Iwanami Shoten|1=Iwanami Shoten}}.</ref>}}
== Ōkuchi no Magamikohara == {{Quotation| Long ago, in the land of Asuka, there was an old wolf that devoured many people. The local villagers feared it and called it {{ill|Ōkuchi no Magami|ja|大口真神|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkuchi no Magami|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=真神}} ("Great-Mouthed True Deity"). The place where it lived was named Ōkuchi no Magamikohara{{refnest|group="Note"|An ancient name for the area near {{ill|Asuka Daibutsu|ja|飛鳥大仏|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Asuka Daibutsu|ja_comment=fixed jawiki redirect|3=飛鳥寺|1=Asuka-dera|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q779755}}, also mentioned in the ''Man'yōshū.''<ref name="taikeip421" />}} as recorded in the Fudoki. | ''Makurakotoba Shokumeishō (Middle)''<ref name="taikei" />}}
== Mitsue Jingū == {{Quotation| The Fudoki states: "In the {{ill|Uda District, Nara|en|Uda District, Nara|WD=Q1131315|lt=Uda District|1=Uda District, Nara}}, in the village of Sasahata{{refnest|group="Note"|Now the Sasabata area of Hara Town, Yamabe 3.<ref name="taikeip421" />}}, stands the shrine of {{ill|Mitsue no Kami|ja|御杖の神|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mitsue no Kami|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. It does not enshrine the Great Spirit{{refnest|group="Note"|Meaning it does not enshrine the spirit of {{ill|Amaterasu|en|Amaterasu|WD=Q455602|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|1=Amaterasu}}.<ref name="taikeip421" />}}. {{ill|Yamatohime-no-mikoto|en|Yamatohime-no-mikoto|WD=Q4388732|lt=Yamatohime-no-Mikoto|1=Yamatohime-no-mikoto}} carried Amaterasu on her head and, with her as the staff, reached this place. After searching for the shrine's location for three months, she finally established the divine fields as {{ill|Kanjin|ja|神戸|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanjin|1=Kobe|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11589706}} (lands belonging to the shrine)." | ''Nihon Shoki Tsūshō, Volume 11''<ref name="taikei" />}}
